        <num>CC 299</num>
        <heading>299.  Time to present excuse</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 299.  Time to present excuse.
The tutor, who has excuses to offer against his appointment, must propose them to the judge who has appointed him, within ten days after he has been acquainted with his appointment, or after the same shall have been notified to him, which period shall be increased one day for every ten miles distance from his residence to the place where his appointment was made, and after this delay he shall no longer be admitted to offer any excuse, unless he has sufficient reason to account for such delay.</p>
        </content>
